          <h2>Financial Reporting</h2>
          <p class="intro">
            When and how Hana reports its results, and where to find the
            underlying documents.
          </p>
        </header>

        <div class="faqgroup">
          <details class="faq">
            <summary><span class="q">When does Hana's financial year end?</span><span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="a">
              <p>Hana's financial year runs from 1 January to 31 December. The company reports results on a quarterly basis (Q1–Q4) in line with SET requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary><span class="q">How often does Hana report results?</span><span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="a">
              <p>Hana publishes quarterly financial statements together with a Management Discussion &amp; Analysis (MD&amp;A), and a full-year Annual Report (Form 56-1 One Report). Each release is announced to the SET and made available on the company's Investor Relations pages.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary><span class="q">Where can I find Hana's annual report and financial statements?</span><span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="a">
              <p>The latest Annual Report (56-1 One Report) is available on the <a href="/investor-relations/annual">Annual Report</a> page. Quarterly statements, MD&amp;A, and investor presentations are on the <a href="/investor-relations/news">Investor News</a> page.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          <details class="faq">
            <summary><span class="q">How can I follow Hana's SET announcements?</span><span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
            <div class="a">
              <p>All official disclosures are filed with the Stock Exchange of Thailand and republished on our <a href="/investor-relations/news">Investor News</a> page as downloadable documents, grouped by year.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

